Key Match Events: Phil Salt launched the first two balls of the England innings for sixes before being bowled third ball in a dramatic start
England chased the fastest-possible win and reached 50-2 from only 3.1 overs
England bowled out Oman for 47 in 13.2 overs
Jos Buttler carried his bat to get England home with 101 balls to spare
Pre-Game Insights: England took a point from its first match against Scotland and was beaten by 36 runs by Australia
England needed quick wickets on June 13 and Archer delivered, capturing his first wicket with the second ball of the second over
Rashid's googly was particularly troublesome for the Oman batters
Post-Match Reflections: England's net run-rate that was minus 1.800 before the match is now plus 3.08, ahead of Scotland's plus 2.164

Buttler said he told the England batters ‘just to be ultra-positive. We'd spoken in the lead-up to this about how we have to win games and if we get the chance we have to try to take advantage of the net run-rate and we managed to do that today’
Miscellaneous Highlights: England needed quick wickets on June 13 and Archer delivered, capturing his first wicket with the second ball of the second over
Archer then dismissed captain Aqib Ilyas in the fourth over when Oman was 16-2
England will now play Namibia on June 16. Its qualification for the Super Eight stage is still dependent on the outcome of the other group match on June 16 between Australia and Scotland
